==English==
===Etymology===
:Old English ''thanc'' (thought, gratitude) of Germanic origin

===Noun===
'''thank'''
# (''Obsolete'') An expression of appreciation, a thought.

===Transitive verb===
'''to thank'''
# To [[express]] [[gratitude]] or [[appreciation]] to someone
#* She '''thanked''' him for the lift
# To [[credit]] or [[hold]] something [[responsible]]
#* We can '''thank''' global warming for this weather

